Pehla, apun ek recursive function bana ke ek disk, source peg, helper peg, and destination peg as input lega. Is function ka naam "hanoi" rakhte hai.

Dusra, base case check karega ki agar disk ek hai toh simply source se destination pe shift kar dega.

Teesra, apun largest disk, n-1 disks ke liye helper peg pe shift karega. Phir, largest disk ko source se destination pe shift karega. Aur finally, helper peg pe remaining n-1 disks ko destination pe shift karega.

Waat lag gayi, algo taiyaar hai! Apun code likh ke dikhata hai:
```
function hanoi(n, source, helper, destination) {
  if (n == 1) {
    // shift single disk from source to destination
    console.log(`Move disk 1 from ${source} to ${destination}`);
    return;
  }

  // move n-1 disks from source to helper
  hanoi(n-1, source, destination, helper);

  // move largest disk from source to destination
  console.log(`Move disk ${n} from ${source} to ${destination}`);

  // move n-1 disks from helper to destination
  hanoi(n-1, helper, source, destination);
}
```
